With [Doubling Season](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doubling Season) out, she comes in with 10 loyalty counters and puts out 6 tokens with 3 loyalty counters left to spare. Her ultimate becomes a "game over" event if it goes off and you can't remove the tokens. I'm not sure it's in the game's best interset for ultimates to be game ending given how easy it is to set them up, especially when people drop planeswalkers so early or use others mechanics to increase the counters (less common). Planeswalkers fit into two categories in this regard then: those that are game changing (their abilities assist you in winning the game), and those that are game ending (their abilities enable you to win the game or make it nigh-impossible for your opponent to win). The planeswalkers in the latter category, while not always the most often used or the most expensive, are the most likely to affect how others perceive you (if you care about that).  

@psychichobo  

